results.name: Decimal expansion of Product_{k>=1} (1-1/5^k).
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1200
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Infinite Product
formula: exp(-Sum_{k>0} sigma_1(k)/(k*5^k)) = exp(-Sum_{k>0} A000203(k)/(k*5^k)). - _Hieronymus Fischer_, Aug 07 2007
Equals (1/5; 1/5)_{infinity}, where (a;q)_{infinity} is the q-Pochhammer symbol. - _G. C. Greubel_, Dec 01 2015
